Head (
Fig. 1
). Vertex, frons, rostrum, and antennae yellowish brown. Antennae 5.5 mm long, filiform with 17 hairy flagellomeres. Eyes brown with some irregular black patches; three ocelli in a triangle, projecting out of head surface in anterior view, shining reddish yellow; front mid ocellus prominently smaller than back lateral ones. Ocellar triangle black, with two long setae closely behind the mid ocellus.
